---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Repl from '../../../components/Repl';
import SchemeRepl from '../../../components/SchemeRepl';
---

<Layout title="Pipeline.lean — Six stages, one cycle" favicon="✏️">
  <main>
    <a href="/reading/lean/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to lean navigator</a>

    <h1>Pipeline.lean</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6"><a href="https://github.com/kimjune01/natural-framework/blob/master/NaturalFramework/Pipeline.lean">View source on GitHub</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Defines the six-stage information processing pipeline from <a href="https://june.kim/the-natural-framework">the Natural Framework</a>: five forward stages (Perceive, Cache, Filter, Attend, Remember) and one backward pass (Consolidate).</p>
    </div>

    <h3>inductive Step</h3>
    <p>An enumeration of the six roles. Five are forward stages that process data sequentially. Consolidate is the backward pass that updates policy inside the substrate.</p>
    <pre class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm text-blue-300"><code><span class="text-blue-300">inductive</span> <span class="text-green-300">Step</span> <span class="text-blue-300">where</span>
  | perceive | cache | filter
  | attend | consolidate | remember</code></pre>

    <h3>structure InterfaceTypes</h3>
    <p>The seven types that flow between pipeline stages: raw input, encoded, indexed, selected, ranked, policy, and persisted. Each stage consumes one type and produces the next.</p>
    <pre class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm text-blue-300"><code><span class="text-blue-300">structure</span> <span class="text-green-300">InterfaceTypes</span> <span class="text-blue-300">where</span>
  raw : Type        -- environment input
  encoded : Type    -- after Perceive
  indexed : Type    -- after Cache
  selected : Type   -- after Filter
  ranked : Type     -- after Attend
  policy : Type     -- parameterizes Attend; written by Consolidate
  persisted : Type  -- after Remember (feeds back to Perceive)</code></pre>

    <h3>structure Pipeline</h3>
    <p>A complete pipeline bundles five forward kernels and one backward kernel. All are monadic &mdash; when the monad is <code>Id</code>, everything is deterministic. Attend takes a policy parameter; Consolidate reads persisted state and updates policy.</p>
    <pre class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm text-blue-300"><code><span class="text-blue-300">structure</span> <span class="text-green-300">Pipeline</span> (M : Type &rarr; Type) [Monad M] (I : InterfaceTypes) <span class="text-blue-300">where</span>
  perceive    : Kernel M I.raw I.encoded
  cache       : Kernel M I.encoded I.indexed
  filter      : Kernel M I.indexed I.selected
  attend      : I.policy &rarr; Kernel M I.selected I.ranked
  remember    : Kernel M I.ranked I.persisted
  consolidate : I.policy &rarr; Kernel M I.persisted I.policy</code></pre>

    <SchemeRepl client:load initialCode={`; The six-stage pipeline as function composition
; Each stage: one type in, one type out

(define (perceive raw)
  (string-append "enc:" raw))

(define (cache encoded)
  (list encoded (string-append encoded "#2")))

(define (filter indexed)
  (list (car indexed)))  ; keep only first

(define (attend policy selected)
  (map (lambda (s) (string-append s "|" policy))
       selected))

(define (remember ranked) ranked)  ; lossless

; Forward pass: compose perceive through attend
(define (forward raw policy)
  (attend policy
    (filter (cache (perceive raw)))))

(display "forward('hello', 'top-1'): ")
(display (forward "hello" "top-1"))
(newline)
(display "forward('hello', 'diverse'): ")
(display (forward "hello" "diverse"))
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:load initialCode={`# The six-stage pipeline as function composition
# Each stage: one type in, one type out

def perceive(raw):
    return "enc:" + raw

def cache(encoded):
    return [encoded, encoded + "#2"]

def filter_stage(indexed):
    return [indexed[0]]  # keep only first

def attend(policy, selected):
    return [s + "|" + policy for s in selected]

def remember(ranked):
    return ranked  # lossless

# Forward pass: compose perceive through attend
def forward(raw, policy):
    return attend(policy, filter_stage(cache(perceive(raw))))

print(f"forward('hello', 'top-1'): {forward('hello', 'top-1')}")
print(f"forward('hello', 'diverse'): {forward('hello', 'diverse')}")
`} />
    </div>

    <h3>def Pipeline.forward</h3>
    <p>The forward data path: raw input flows through Perceive, Cache, Filter, and Attend (parameterized by current policy), producing ranked output. Written as explicit binds for proof tractability (easier for Lean to unfold).</p>

    <h3>def Pipeline.cycle</h3>
    <p>One full cycle: run the forward pass, persist the result via Remember, then run Consolidate to derive updated policy. Returns the new policy and persisted state as a pair.</p>

    <h3>def Pipeline.iterate</h3>
    <p>Run the pipeline n times over a stream of inputs. Each iteration chains via bind, threading the policy through cycles.</p>

